The paper proposes a probabilistic model for interpreting gene expression levels observed through single-cell RNA sequencing. The model uses neural networks to specify conditional distributions and employs variational inference and stochastic optimization to approximate the posterior distribution. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) and statistics (stat.ML). Additionally, the paper deals with biological data and proposes a Bayesian hypothesis test for differential expression, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of quantitative methods in biology (q-bio.QM) and genomics (q-bio.GN).
